parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause extended stopping distances, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light comes on
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the vehicle experiences extended stopping distances
the brakes fail to respond
the vehicle glides forward even after brakes are applied
the brakes lock up
and the vehicle slides or loses control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brake pedal to feel soft or spongy, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle is unable to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Suspension Failure due to Rust
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates
sways
or pulls to one side while driving
especially at high speeds. The rear suspension arm or bracket may break off
causing the vehicle to lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can cause structural failure, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The frame is severely rusted
with holes and corrosion
causing the vehicle to vibrate or sway while driving. The rear suspension may break off
and the vehicle may be unable to pass inspection.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake issues can cause extended stopping distances, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
and the brake pedal may feel soft or spongy. The brake warning light may illuminate
and the vehicle may vibrate or shake when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system issues can cause the vehicle to shut off while driving, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle may shut off while driving
and the engine may rev constantly. The vehicle may not start properly
and the electrical system may malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A leaking fuel tank can cause fuel to spill onto the road, creating a fire hazard and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Fuel tank leaking abnormally
underframe severely rusted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An inaccurate fuel gauge can lead to unexpected fuel depletion, stranding the driver, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Fuel gauge reads wrongly
does not register a full tank of gas
drops to empty when the tank is full

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning rear beverage holder can cause tripping hazards, especially for children, and potentially lead to injuries.

opens up on its own

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause unexpected loss of power, potentially leading to accidents.

can be restarted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can cause the vehicle to become unstable, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.

corroded

the vehicle to sway or lose control
